Subject: What Have You Read?
Description: What's something amazing that you read recently that you want to tell the world about?  Speakers include:Jim Leach, Andrea Johnson, Stewart Sternberg, Nicole Castle - Track: Literature  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Editing for Your Spouse/Partner/BFF/Pet
Description:
'Can you read this and tell me what you think?' is a question to test any relationship.
 We will learn some ways to navigate that communications mine-field while musing on the nature of editing, the care and feeding of your larval writer and some small, practical steps towards upping our editing game.  Speakers include:Scott Favre, Clif Flynt, Janice Leach, Jim Leach - Track: Literature  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Poetry Starter Kit
Description: Audience Participation Panel: Speculative Poetry Starter Kit: who to read, where to look and exactly what the heck IS speculative poetry.  Speakers include:Jim Leach, Sean Davis - Track: Literature  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Writing Fast and Slow
Description: Are you a hack if you write quickly? Are you an amateur if you write slowly? How many books a year should a working writer produce, and how has that expectation changed in today’s publishing climate? How quickly do readers want—or expect—the next book?  Speakers include:Alex Kourvo, Jen Haeger, Jim Leach, Cathrynne Valente - Track: Literature  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Speak Your Words
Description: We are all made of stories and sharing them can be powerful and life changing. Come and share our version of an open mic night.  Bring your self-written poetry, personal manifesto, or short-short story.  Speakers include:Jim Leach, Matt Betts, Sean Davis, Jessica Roland - Track: Literature  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none
